race.comment: AQUAFOX (1) took a sharp step forward second-up here, charging late and falling narrowly short. Peaking now third-up and sticks with the claimer, keeping him nicely in at the weights again. Ready to win. LA PETITE (12) has lifted noticeably in her past two runs and should be nearing her top. She'll stalk the speed from a handy position and be poised to pounce turning for home. IT'S A SOLID DEEL (5) rattled home to just edge out AQUAFOX here 12 days ago. If he can settle a touch closer, he's a genuine winning hope. NOUVEAU MARCHE (7) also comes through that same race, finishing only half a length further back. Third-up and fitter again, he's right in the mix.
